He's no respecter of persons.

00:51:00.800 --> 00:51:10.040
You may be the best quilt maker out there and He'll teach you a different way to make a better quilt.

00:51:19.613 --> 00:51:19.907
You could be the best cowboy.

00:51:29.120 --> 00:51:29.640
You say, 'Well, I work with cows; I work with pigs; I work with whatever.

00:51:29.640 --> 00:51:37.107
' I know we're not supposed to eat pork, but it's interesting—He'll talk to you about chickens.

00:51:37.107 --> 00:51:39.470
He'll talk to you about sheep.

00:51:39.470 --> 00:51:51.220
He'll talk about, 'Hey, if you plant this over here a little bit different, that'll grow better because that soil is a little bit...

00:51:51.220 --> 00:52:03.168
it's only 10 feet away, but that right there is a good spot.

00:52:04.440 --> 00:52:06.997
If you plant that right there, it'll grow better.

00:52:06.997 --> 00:52:09.715
' It doesn't matter.

00:52:09.715 --> 00:52:10.775
Practice His presence.

00:52:10.775 --> 00:52:17.536
Whatever He tells you to do, do it and you'll be blessed.

00:52:17.536 --> 00:52:28.056
People get ticked off at me all the time because He tells me investments.

00:52:34.213 --> 00:52:34.387
He does.

00:52:34.387 --> 00:52:36.700
And people get mad when they see I get blessed.

00:52:45.610 --> 00:52:45.905
But if you are with Jesus, He'll tell you things.

00:53:02.560 --> 00:53:02.870
So don't get mad at me when I get blessed.

00:53:10.108 --> 00:53:11.042
I talk about it all the time to my family.

00:53:13.445 --> 00:53:16.194
I said, 'Listen, this is what the Lord said to do.

00:53:16.194 --> 00:53:23.000
' And do you know I've tried to obey Him every single step of the way?

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:27.183
Even when people go, 'Well, who are you?

00:53:27.183 --> 00:53:37.714
' Do you know I used to stand in front of some of the biggest businessmen in all of a place and they would ask me questions?

00:53:37.714 --> 00:53:40.416
Now, do I have everything always down?

00:53:40.416 --> 00:53:44.860
But people can see when you've been with Jesus.

00:53:45.640 --> 00:53:55.520
I know I can miss it, but I just marvel because He has a topic about everything.

00:53:59.520 --> 00:54:00.048
He'll talk about the birds, the flowers, He'll talk...

00:54:09.392 --> 00:54:09.944
I love my flowers, ferns, and greenery.

00:54:09.944 --> 00:54:31.060
I'll spend hours just being quiet, and I teach my little girl, Paisley; she'll come up beside me and I say, 'Listen, if you're going to be in this zone, this is where we don't talk.

00:54:31.060 --> 00:54:37.420
This is where we listen.

00:54:37.420 --> 00:54:42.415
' And I teach her to listen.

00:54:42.415 --> 00:54:45.720
This is not where we talk.

00:54:45.720 --> 00:54:49.540
I spend time in quiet.

00:54:51.610 --> 00:54:52.300
You have to be quiet.

00:55:12.458 --> 00:55:12.836
God is not going to compete with you.

00:55:16.211 --> 00:55:19.244
He's not going to try to overpower you.

00:55:19.244 --> 00:55:22.965
He's a gentleman, but if you're always running your mouth, He's not going to talk.

00:55:22.965 --> 00:55:23.315
Shh.

00:55:23.315 --> 00:55:27.268
Be still when you're outside.

00:55:27.268 --> 00:55:28.648
He'll talk to you.

00:55:28.648 --> 00:55:37.467
And I always make an atmosphere for Him to speak to me.

00:55:37.467 --> 00:55:40.552
And I'll pray in the Spirit.

00:55:40.552 --> 00:55:42.509
Just pray softly.

00:55:49.669 --> 00:55:59.280
You don't have to be yelling in tongues with everybody in the neighborhood looking at you going, 'What is going on with that dude?

00:55:59.280 --> 00:56:03.360
' I just pray softly to myself.

00:56:03.360 --> 00:56:04.040
Worship.

00:56:04.040 --> 00:56:04.720
Worship.

00:56:04.720 --> 00:56:06.463
Thank You, Jesus.

00:56:09.120 --> 00:56:12.960
I try to continually stay in the flow of the river because I told Diana it's always flowing.

00:56:12.960 --> 00:56:13.600
He's always talking.

00:56:13.600 --> 00:56:19.480
The Holy Spirit is always talking to you and leading you.

00:56:19.480 --> 00:56:22.750
There's no end to it if you are sensitive to it.

00:56:22.750 --> 00:56:23.995
He'll tell you everything.

00:56:23.995 --> 00:56:34.600
All that you say in word and deed, we give all to the glory of God.

00:56:34.600 --> 00:56:39.228
I even talked to Pastor Chip.

00:56:50.816 --> 00:56:51.264
He said, "You know, Brandon, he'll even tell you about sports.

00:56:51.264 --> 00:56:53.135
" I said, "Yes, he does.

00:56:53.525 --> 00:56:54.480
He talks about sports, Pastor.

00:56:54.860 --> 00:57:00.686
" And he, Pastor Chip, is a coach at heart, Champions for Christ.

00:57:00.686 --> 00:57:04.985
He's all into it, and he loves to talk about sports.

00:57:04.985 --> 00:57:06.085
He loves baseball.

00:57:06.085 --> 00:57:08.938
He loves things like that, you know, football.

00:57:08.938 --> 00:57:10.680
He loves the Chicago Bears.

00:57:21.680 --> 00:57:22.213
And the Lord will sit down and just listen and talk about things: "How do you become better?

00:57:22.213 --> 00:57:37.110
" He wants you to be a champion on every single level of your life—to be the head and not the tail, above and not beneath.

00:57:54.360 --> 00:57:54.580
But we have made him into some kind of religious figure that we can't talk to.

00:57:54.580 --> 00:58:04.460
And God is an ever-present help in a time of need.

00:58:17.644 --> 00:58:17.849
And guess what?

00:58:28.450 --> 00:58:28.715
I'm always in need of him.

00:58:29.510 --> 00:58:32.480
I don't think I ever don't need him.

00:58:32.480 --> 00:58:33.680
Do you?

00:58:33.680 --> 00:58:35.605
Do you not need him?

00:58:35.605 --> 00:58:42.800
If you don't, you're in trouble.

00:58:42.800 --> 00:58:46.520
He's an ever-present help in a time of need.

00:58:46.520 --> 00:58:51.520
I'm always in need of him.

00:58:51.520 --> 00:58:55.600
I don't care who you are; I need him in everything.

00:58:55.600 --> 00:59:04.270
Tell me, teach me how to drive my car better to get better gas mileage.

00:59:04.280 --> 00:59:11.040
Teach me when I'm going down, and he'll say, "You know, you didn't handle that real well.

00:59:11.040 --> 00:59:15.280
" He just corrected me even on how I was cranky with Braden just a second ago.

00:59:15.280 --> 00:59:19.369
He said, "You owe an apology.

00:59:19.369 --> 00:59:24.417
Oh, you owe him an apology.

00:59:29.040 --> 00:59:29.267
" I'm sorry, Braden; I shouldn't be so cranky.

00:59:29.267 --> 00:59:30.173
It's the truth.

00:59:30.173 --> 00:59:37.240
He corrects me all the time, but he's always tugging my heart: "You need to be more kind.

00:59:46.245 --> 00:59:46.390
You need to be more patient.

00:59:46.535 --> 00:59:53.130
You need to walk in love.

01:00:02.817 --> 01:00:03.000
" I'm always wanting to incline my ear to him so that my kids learn to operate the same way.

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:05.010
And you know what?

01:00:05.010 --> 01:00:07.935
He has an opinion about everybody I talk to.

01:00:07.935 --> 01:00:16.013
There's some people I get off the phone with and he says, "They're in trouble.

01:00:16.013 --> 01:00:20.440
They won't make it because they're not doing this and this and this.

01:00:22.304 --> 01:00:25.170
" I said, "Well, what do you—it's none of your business.

01:00:25.170 --> 01:00:27.107
They didn't ask for your advice.

01:00:27.107 --> 01:00:28.512
They didn't ask for your advice.

01:00:28.704 --> 01:00:37.160
And if you gave them your advice, it's not them getting it from me; it's getting it from you.

01:00:37.160 --> 01:00:39.984
" There's so much correction about it.

01:00:42.640 --> 01:00:42.977
But he always has an opinion about everything.

01:00:46.007 --> 01:00:47.045
And I love how he talks about Billy Burke.

01:00:47.410 --> 01:00:55.520
I know, y'all, every time I talk to the Lord—that's my friend—and I am not a person who brown-noses.

01:00:56.720 --> 01:00:58.990
I tell you that; I'm just telling you the flat truth.

01:00:58.990 --> 01:01:00.575
He'll say, "That's my friend.

01:01:06.690 --> 01:01:07.240
" This is what this is, and the way he instructs about certain people.

01:01:08.340 --> 01:01:10.773
If he ever says—and there's times he has—"I don't know them.

01:01:11.440 --> 01:01:11.751
I don't know them.

01:01:11.751 --> 01:01:13.620
What they're saying is a lie.

01:01:13.620 --> 01:01:14.947
They're fake.

01:01:14.947 --> 01:01:15.767
They're two-faced.

01:01:15.767 --> 01:01:20.000
They're not all in for me.

01:01:20.000 --> 01:01:21.240
Be cautious of them.

01:01:28.027 --> 01:01:28.253
" And he'll say certain things to me, warning me, "Protect yourself against that individual.

01:01:28.253 --> 01:01:30.080
Don't allow him in too close.

01:01:30.080 --> 01:01:32.080
" What does he say about you?

01:01:32.080 --> 01:01:34.540
Are you thinking you're hiding something from him?

01:01:46.653 --> 01:01:47.000
When you're trying to hide stuff from everybody else, maybe they can't see it, but he can.

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:53.076
What do you display in the spirit realm and your fragrance?

01:01:53.076 --> 01:01:54.564
What is your fragrance?

01:01:54.564 --> 01:01:56.246
Do you stink?

01:01:58.960 --> 01:02:06.200
And the only way we're upright and the only way we're able to be right is by always being underneath that blood.

01:02:25.467 --> 01:02:25.760
I take communion all the time.

01:02:41.747 --> 01:02:42.022
And I know God, I can't do this on my own.

01:02:45.640 --> 01:02:50.640
So if he's warning him about me and somebody said, "Well, Brandon, this is what we say about you.

01:02:50.640 --> 01:02:52.680
" I'm not here to lie to you.

01:03:12.320 --> 01:03:12.538
I know I realize I've got something I'm going through.

01:03:12.538 --> 01:03:18.820
But I ask him to search me and know me: "Create in me a clean heart.

01:03:18.820 --> 01:03:21.635
Fix it.

01:03:21.635 --> 01:03:22.910
Fix it.

01:03:22.920 --> 01:03:26.220
" But I want when I get done that just like they marveled.

01:03:26.220 --> 01:03:30.310
They marveled because they had been with Jesus.

01:03:39.760 --> 01:03:39.970
Do people marvel after you leave because you have been with Jesus?

01:03:39.970 --> 01:03:42.850
Or do they say, "Man, she is a Sister Clipboard.

01:03:42.850 --> 01:03:46.549
Woo, that girl right there has a Jezebel spirit.

01:03:46.549 --> 01:03:49.736
Does she have a Delilah spirit?

01:03:49.736 --> 01:03:55.942
Does she have, or does he have some kind of—I have to go and take a bath.

01:03:55.942 --> 01:04:04.840
" I feel nothing, and I can walk up to a sweet old lady in the back row and she has presence.

01:04:04.840 --> 01:04:08.940
She's just an intercessor in the church, a sweet little black lady.

01:04:08.940 --> 01:04:14.880
He told me about a sweet little black lady; she walked to him and he said, "My goodness, lady, you have it.

01:04:14.880 --> 01:04:15.863
" You know why?

01:04:15.863 --> 01:04:17.100
Because presence knows presence.

01:04:17.100 --> 01:04:19.200
Does it make sense what I'm saying?

01:04:19.200 --> 01:04:20.000
Is it okay?

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:20.973
Presence knows presence.

01:04:20.973 --> 01:04:34.044
And that sweet little black lady on the back row of this building—his meeting he was holding—he walked up to this woman and he grabbed a hold of her hand.

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:42.298
And the moment he grabbed her hand, there was impartation because what she was carrying was what he was carrying.

01:04:46.051 --> 01:04:46.394
And iron sharpens iron.

01:04:58.160 --> 01:04:58.355
But you can always tell when somebody's been with Jesus.

01:05:08.008 --> 01:05:08.584
And this was just a little old lady.

01:05:08.584 --> 01:05:13.620
It wasn't the big preacher on the front row.

01:05:13.620 --> 01:05:17.600
It was a little old lady.

01:05:17.600 --> 01:05:18.965
She had been with Jesus.

01:05:23.304 --> 01:05:23.428
And you can marvel at it.

01:05:23.428 --> 01:05:33.875
So I don't care if you're sitting on the back row or the front row or in between.

01:05:33.875 --> 01:05:41.160
Fragrance and presence follows you.

01:05:41.160 --> 01:05:47.400
When you stay with Jesus, there's no pretending.

01:05:53.013 --> 01:05:53.427
You can't pray at it.

01:05:53.427 --> 01:05:56.600
It is a fragrance and it is a taste.

01:05:56.600 --> 01:05:59.280
What does your fruit taste like?

01:06:22.371 --> 01:06:31.349
What do you—"Taste and see that the Lord is good"—but what do people taste when they're around you?

01:06:31.349 --> 01:06:37.920
Insecurity, pride, jealousy, bitterness, anger, or all the fruits of the Spirit?

01:06:54.120 --> 01:06:54.320
What do they taste when they're around you?

01:07:11.080 --> 01:07:11.320
What fragrance do you bring when you walk in a room?

01:07:19.418 --> 01:07:19.651
You can tell when there's strife in a room.

01:07:19.651 --> 01:07:28.840
When you're bickering with your wife and you come in a room, you can tell when an atmosphere is charged with anger.

01:07:34.520 --> 01:07:34.795
You can go, "There's something bad been up in here.

01:07:34.795 --> 01:07:35.895
Something's going on.

01:07:35.895 --> 01:07:46.240
" I can walk into a house that I'm looking at and I can feel critters, and I can feel them push on you and I say, "Uh, there's devils in this house.

01:07:46.240 --> 01:07:47.733
" They know when I'm there.

01:07:47.733 --> 01:08:00.600
But when I walk in a house and you feel the presence and you go, "There's such a sweet fragrance.

01:08:01.745 --> 01:08:10.504
" We had an individual come by and eat dinner with us and they sat on the couch and they fell asleep.

01:08:10.504 --> 01:08:14.171
I try very hard to keep strife out.

01:08:21.857 --> 01:08:23.794
You let that fragrance and even when I say, "What do you feel when you come to my house?

01:08:23.794 --> 01:08:31.240
What do you feel when you go to somebody else's house?

01:08:31.240 --> 01:08:37.240
" When they walk in your home, what do you feel?

01:08:37.240 --> 01:08:39.040
Do demons push against you?

01:08:39.040 --> 01:08:41.156
Have you let critters in your house?

01:08:41.156 --> 01:08:44.050
What is so tangible in your home?

01:08:44.050 --> 01:08:47.445
I've been into some houses I can't wait to leave.

01:08:47.445 --> 01:08:53.960
I'm like, "I have got to get out of here.

01:08:53.960 --> 01:08:56.103
" I've been into churches that I feel that.

01:08:56.103 --> 01:09:02.590
I said, "I got to get out of here right now.

01:09:16.279 --> 01:09:16.782
" It pushes.

01:09:16.782 --> 01:09:36.520
But I'm trying to tell you, when you have him, there is a peace that passes all understanding and there's so much love and there's so much joy that will overflow your life, but you will be a carrier of it.

01:09:48.296 --> 01:09:49.088
You can feel presence.

01:09:49.088 --> 01:09:52.996
That's what I'm trying to tell you.

01:09:52.996 --> 01:09:56.970
Out of the overflow, that's why I try to be around certain people.

01:09:56.970 --> 01:10:04.987
I say, "My goodness, I feel his presence around you.

01:10:04.987 --> 01:10:06.496
I'll sow into it.

01:10:06.496 --> 01:10:18.565
" I'm always curious about when somebody gives me money, especially when somebody wants to bless my family on this channel and I pray.

01:10:19.330 --> 01:10:20.560
I never ask for a dime.

01:10:32.691 --> 01:10:32.960
Never ask for a dime and never will.

01:10:32.960 --> 01:10:38.777
But there's people that feel led to give to us and say, "Hey, I feel led to help you.

01:10:39.920 --> 01:10:40.165
" And I say, "Okay.

01:10:40.165 --> 01:10:43.613
" But I always take and pray over their stuff.

01:11:13.051 --> 01:11:20.400
And I spend a lot of time and my wife will write them a letter or whatever, but I lay my hands on it and I intercede and I ask for God to multiply it because I look at it as special that somebody would work really hard to try to help me.

01:11:20.400 --> 01:11:40.060
So I always take it, and my kids—Paisley and my son and everybody—we all lay hands on it, take communion over it, and I pray over the money and I say, "God, bless this.

01:11:40.060 --> 01:11:48.018
" But I never know if my ground's good because how do you test your own ground?

01:11:48.018 --> 01:12:13.480
But I had a lady write a letter today and she said, "Ever since I started blessing your ministry, I've paid off all this stuff.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I paid off my boat.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
" "I paid off my RV that I had.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
" She said, "I'm almost completely debt-free or whatever it was.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
I paid for all this stuff, and she said, 'I'm only a little bit until I'm debt-free with my house.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
'" And she said, "I believe it was because we gave to the ground.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
" That blessed me a lot today.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Like I said, I'm always curious about it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
I know when I sow into certain ground, I know good ground.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
I test everybody's ground, and if I don't see good fruit in that ground, I don't give there.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
I don't always try to be polite about it; I'm just real.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Because the Lord always said to me, "Brandon, don't ever give out of a feeling of necessity into certain ground.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
Always give whenever you're led by me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Money with a mission.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
Sow where I tell you to sow because not all ground will produce.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
Some ground is full of rocks.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
Some ground doesn't produce at all.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
But I want you to be strategic in your giving and the soil that I tell you to give into.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
" So I pray about it a lot, and I sow into the ground.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
There's some ground that I give to and I never get fruit back—not very much.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
But then he says, "Give over here," and it's fresh manure, and I'll get back a good harvest.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
He'll give me an idea.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
He'll tell me, "Go to this thrift store," and usually it's in Edmond.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
"I want you to drive there.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
" And there's a bunch of Brioni, a bunch of Chanel, and a bunch of this.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
A lady just dropped it off.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
"I want you to go in there, and you're going to make enough to pay all your bills for the month.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
" I pray in the spirit and the Lord says, "Go over there.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
" So I sow the seed and I believe for my need.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
The Lord says, "I want you to buy that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
There's a lawnmower over here that is a good Honda lawnmower and you can flip it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Put it on Craigslist.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
" So, I buy it for real cheap at the garage sale, put it on Craigslist, and flip it, making a couple hundred bucks.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
It's just following his voice.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
That's why I'm always pressing and asking him, "Show me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
" Then he started teaching me about crypto and about other things like cars.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
"This car over here, you can flip that car.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
It just needs a timing belt.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.150
" There have been times he'll say, "The man with the white shirt is going to knock on the door, and that's the man who will buy the car today.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
" I see the man with the white shirt.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
He's a Spanish man.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
He said, "This Hispanic man will knock on the door.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
" I paid $800 for the car back then.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
My dad put the new timing belt on it and whatever else it needed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I sold it for $3,500.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
This was years ago, and that's how it's always happened.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
I listen.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
If you have an art of listening and praying, he'll teach you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
But a lot of people are always looking for a handout.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
They're always looking for that mailbox mentality of a miracle because of what you've been taught at the charismatic shake and bake.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I'm not into all that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
I sow into strategic ground, and I believe that God will bless my hands.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I'm not looking to people for a handout.

